@marraduse2519 вАЛ Where did I criticise Orwell's works?  None of that changes what he wrote or that he intended it as allegory, sufficiently to identify which real figures his major characters represented.
The 2 works don't criticise communism at all.   They don't even criticise socialism as such.  They criticize socialists in one case and socialist revolutionaries in the other.  Communism does not even feature in 1984, and was only very briefly if at all achieved in Animal Farm.  
"right wing politicians can pretend to be communists in order to make communism look like something it isn't." - There was nothing anywhere in either of the works even similar to this.  Communism requires zero politicians.  We are discussing here socialist elites, not communism.

